Validations:
    - AngularJS supports the form validations by default.

    - when ever error raised in form, automatically corresponding
      errors will be stored into $error object.

    - "$error" is the predefined object and holds the forms
       related errors.

Ex.
    <form name="myForm">
        <input type="text"
               name="uname"
               ng-model="uname"
               ng-minlength="3"
               ng-maxlength="6"
               required>

        <h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.minlength">***Minimum 3 Characters Are Required****</h5>
        <h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.maxlength">***Maximum 6 Chacaters are Allowed***</h5>
        <h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.required">***Can't Left Blank***</h5>

    </form>




Validations By using ngMessages Module:
---------------------------------------

    - ngMessages is the predefined module used to
      overcome the data redundancy.


Steps to create the Validations by using ngMessages Module
----------------------------------------------------------

Step 1:
    download ngMessages Module by using bower.

[Note : "angular-messages" is the bower key
         used to download the "ngMessages" module dependency
         file]


Step 2:
    add the dependency

var app = angular.module("app",["ngMessages"]);



Step3:
    create the validations by using "ng-message" directive
    in external template


Ex.
    messages.html


Step 4:
    import external template by using "ng-messages" &
                                      "ng-messages-include"
                                      directives





